Former BayernLB Chief Gribkowsky in Blackmail Probe, SZ Says

-- B y   E v a   v o n   S c h a p e r
-- 
2011-04-30T13:29:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/former-bayernlb-chief-gribkowsky-in-blackmail-probe-sz-says.html
Munich prosecutors are
investigating Bayerische Landesbank’s former chief executive
officer Gerhard Gribkowsky on blackmail charges,  Focus  magazine
said, citing people close to legal circles.  Gribkowsky is said to have threatened Formula One
Management Ltd. Chief Executive Officer Bernie Ecclestone with a
tax probe if he didn’t agree to pay Gribkowsky more than $40
million in connection the sale of a Formula One stake, the paper
said  Ecclestone was questioned by Munich prosecutors on April 6
and is now being investigated for aiding a breach of trust, the
newspaper said in a preview of an article for tomorrow’s
edition. The case is part of a probe into allegations banker
Gerhard Gribkowsky may have taken a $50 million kickback for
engineering the sale of Formula One to CVC Capital Partners Ltd,
the paper said.  Matthias Priwitzer, a spokesman for BayernLB, declined to
comment in a telephone interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eva von Schaper in Munich at 
 evonschaper@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net  